# devbox session-secrets manifest — materialize vault projects into app .env files
# at login (on tmpfs/RAM), wiped at the last logout. Copy to deploy/secrets.map
# (gitignored) and edit. `configure`/`up` installs it onto the box when present.
#
# One mapping per line:
#
#   <vault-project>   <absolute dest .env path on the box>
#
#   project = the name you `devbox vault load <project>` (stored at secret/<project>,
#             and the filename in your local ./secrets/<project>.env)
#   dest    = where your app reads its .env on the box. Parent dirs are auto-created;
#             the file there becomes a symlink into RAM. Must be an absolute path.
#
# The project name and the dest filename are independent — so many apps can each use a
# plain ".env" (the directory disambiguates); you only need a distinct project label.
#
# Example:
#   frontend   /home/eddyg/apps/frontend/.env
#   backend    /home/eddyg/apps/backend/.env
#   worker     /home/eddyg/services/worker/.env
#
# Notes:
# - The vault must be UNSEALED (from your laptop: `devbox vault unseal`) for materialize
#   to run. If sealed at login, it's skipped with a notice; after unsealing run
#   `systemctl --user restart devbox-secrets` on the box.
# - Cleanup only removes our symlink + the RAM copy — never a real file you placed there,
#   and never your local ./secrets or the vault.
